title: No way to filter on an anchored regexp like /^AT/
body:
There is no way to filter on an anchored regexp like "^AT". All one can
do is filter on "AT" which includes regexp ".*AT".

title: Add an Intent so other apps can use Catlog to send logcat info via email
body:
Sorry, my GitHub skills are approx. zero. I think this pull request probably includes the one I sent you yesterday.

Anyway, I've added an Intent to Catlog so other apps can use it to send logcat info by email. It's not as good as I was hoping - the user is still prompted by the email program to click on Send. I would prefer that it was completely automatic, but that is apparently not possible, or at least not easy.

Hope you can use this.

body:
1. Sorry for the delay.
2. I don't use GitHub very much, so I hope I'm doing this "pull request" thing correctly.
3. I don't use Eclipse. I have coded and tested this with IntelliJ IDEA, and it looks like it works.
4. The formatting of the code is all off because I use spaces instead of tabs. 

Despite all of the above, I hope you can use this. Thanks again for making Catlog available.

title: Put "findFilterItems" into background thread in LogcatActivity.java
body: See  nolanlawson/Catlog#42

title: Put invocation to "findFilterItems" into AsyncTask in LogcatActivity.java?
body:
Hi developers of Catlog,

I'm a Ph.D. student and I'm doing research on improving performance 
for Android apps.

In Catlog, "CatlogDBHelper.findFilterItems" accesses database,
so you put the invocation of this method into AsyncTask at line 593 of
LogcatActivity.java ("showFiltersDialog" method) to improve
responsiveness.

But there are two other places in LogcatActivity.java where you still
invoke "CatlogDBHelper.findFilterItems" in UI thread.
"addFiltersToSuggestions" calls "findFilterItems" at line 186 and it's
eventually called by two "onPreExecute" methods at line 1906 and 1290.
"onPreExecute" is executed by UI thread.

Why don't you also put all invocations to "findFilterItems" into background
thread? Is there any specific reason?

Thanks,
Yu

title: Include Android_ID in device_info.txt
body:
Thanks for creating CatLog and making it available.

I'm not all that well-versed in Android development, but would it not be a good idea to include Android_ID in the device_info.txt file?

http://developer.android.com/reference/android/provider/Settings.Secure.html#ANDROID_ID
http://android-developers.blogspot.com/2011/03/identifying-app-installations.html
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2785485/is-there-a-unique-android-device-id

I envisage a situation where my app will be deployed on dozens, maybe hundreds, of devices that are more-or-less identical, and it could be an advantage to keep track of which device (and thus which user) has had a reported problem.

Thanks.

title: "Open" a saved log and current view keeps flooding with current log entries
body:
I open a saved log and the current view keeps flooding me with current log entries.

Actions to replicate are simple:
1. Save any log file for about 30 seconds. Quit the program, flush it out of memory (long press home and clear the app)
2. Run the app and Open the log file.
3. It keeps flooding you with current log actions and wont let you view the log you opened.

title: Add "Copy to Clipboard" into context menu of Log-Entry
body:
Hi,

I'm using the app to create bug-reports for one of my apps. This requires me to copy the log-entry to clipboard and then add it into my bugtracker. As I could not find any option, to copy a single entry, I modified the app to feature a context menu (instead of a "OnLongListItemClick") which contains the option to copy the entry or use the "old" Search-By filter.
If you like this change, feel free to include it into the app, I think it might help others too.

Greetings

PS: thanks for the app!

title: Lines with log level "fatal" not parsed correctly
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
Reported by a user:
aLogcat seems to no longer work correctly, so I searched for a replacement and found your app, but I think there is an error in the parser. I played a bit and set the log level to fatal. Below you see what I got. Those additional lines also were pain text and not in the tabular format.
I've set the log level to fatal but as you can see, I also got messages from other log levels displayed. Those messages also didn't show in the tabular layout with color coded log level etc. but as a simple text line, so I guess the parser didn't recognize the format of those log lines correctly.

title: no log appears
body: On my S4 with WanamLite ROM, with CatLog's default settings, the spinner spins forever and nothing ever appears in window. The spinner continues to spin even after hitting the pause button. Record proceeds without error, but no file gets saved, presumably because it would be empty. The strange thing is that, at one point, CatLog did display and save (I uploaded a log here at GtiHub). But even then, the pause button didn't work, though everything thing else seemed functional. I also get the same failure with aLogCat, so it's apparently something on my phone. Any suggestions? Do you have a forum on xda where you answer this kind of maintenance question?

title: Add ACCESS_SUPERUSER to permissions list
body:
Feature request: add support for ACCESS_SUPERUSER permission as supported by koush's Superuser app. [1]
This can be accomplished by adding this line to AndroidManifest.xml :

`<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_SUPERUSER" />`

[1] https://plus.google.com/103583939320326217147/posts/T9xnMJEnzf1

title: Softkeyboard not hiding after selecting a suggested search-term in the list
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
Softkeyboard not hiding after selecting a suggested search-term in the list

This is not a bug, i think it is missing feature.

Let's say i want to enter some text to search the log entries for. A keyboard pops ups, and when i start for example with "teth" then theres some activities listed containing the word tethering. So i click on one of those suggested terms, and it succesfully lists the log entries for this term. But the keyboard, that previously got opened, doesn't close. But i am finished looking for what i was seeking.

title: Thousands of entries scrolling down the screen that show TextLayoutCache
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
From a user:
When I start Catlog there seems to be thousands of entries scrolling down the screen that show TextLayoutCache. (See attached screen shot). I got the PID number from the Catlog screen then looked up the PID number in a task manager and it showed that it was the Catlog process that was creating all the log entries. I killed the Catlog process and then went back in and the messages were no longer displaying. But I've had this problem on numerous occasions, on different days, and I turn my phone off every night. So it seems to be a reoccurring problem, but doesn't happen all the time. In the attached log search for TextLayoutCache. The PID number was 17403 for the Catlog process.

title: Support for devices without touch screens
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body: Devices such as e.g. Google TV should probably be supported.  CatLog is designed to be a universal Android log reader, so I can't imagine why I wouldn't include all devices.

title: Changing text size setting causes incorrect truncation
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body:
See screenshot.  Changing the text size to "extra large" and then back to normal seems to result in the text getting truncated at the wrong spot.

I assume this is because of some static variable somewhere that I'm not properly resetting when the settings are changed.

![2013-01-20 16 39 42](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/283842/81323/33e4d42c-6318-11e2-9bda-727c8cd64201.png)

title: Consider making the widget itself configurable for filters
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body: Right now filters have to be chosen each time the widget is launched.  This is a little cumbersome.  Perhaps we could make the widget itself configurable?  This suggestion came from a user.

title: Auto-store logs in Dropbox
body:
This was a request given by a user: 

```
auto copy logs (when done) to dropbox - much easier to look at the logs on a pc
```

title: improve Japanese translation
body:
Hi,

I tried to improve Japanese translation to more natural one.
Please integrate this improvement if you think it nice.

title: Tag-Filter with spaces doesn't work
body:
I tried to create a log for "Changelog Droid" by long-tapping an entry from it and filtering by the tag "Changelog Droid". This resulted in an empty list. The filter bar on top reads "tag:Changelog Droid" and my guess is that it doesn't work because of the space. I also tried tag:"Changelog Droid" without success. And even tag:Changelog doesn't work.

Apps without spaces in their names work, e.g. tag:dalvikvm .

This is on Jelly Bean 4.1.2 (stock ROM) on a Galaxy Nexus.

title: Swedish translation
body:
Hi,
Feel free to use the swedish translation that I have made.

title: Colors should be more pleasing to the eye
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body:
The colors I'm using now were chosen by trial and error.  I should have used methods like the ones described here:

http://devmag.org.za/2012/07/29/how-to-choose-colours-procedurally-algorithms/
http://martin.ankerl.com/2009/12/09/how-to-create-random-colors-programmatically/

title: Cannot stop recording on JellyBean
label: [Label(name="bug")]

1) Hit Recording button

Expected result: notification goes away, recording stops
Actual result: app crashes

title: Add email address as an Intent request parameter, and/or return log lines to the source app
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body: Idea from a user: specify the email address in the CatLog external intent, to make it easier for end users to email developers.  Alternatively, allow the intent to return a slice of the log to the calling app, so the calling app can handle it itself.

title: Random OutOfMemory errors
label: [Label(name="bug")]
body: These still seem to pop up from time to time.  It might be worth looking into using Strings more efficiently.

title: Add Help section
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body:
How do I send a bug report to a developer?

1) Hit Menu, then Record.
2) Open the other app, and do whatever caused the bug.
3) Go back to CatLog, hit Menu, then Stop Recording.
4) Hit Menu, then Send, then email the bug to the developer.

How do I do an advanced filter?

...

How do I start CatLog from within my own app?

...

title: Add Lucene-style -text:foo syntax
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body: This would allow users to create negation queries, i.e. queries that match log lines that DON'T contain a particular piece of text.

title: Fix bug where logs get spliced if you change the log buffer
body: Go to settings, change the log buffer, then go back.  Logs from the previous buffer will appear in the current buffer.  Seems to be a race condition similar to the problem with opening files.

title: Fix bug where "open" sometimes does not include the actual log
body:
Steps to reproduce on an ICS emulator:

Start up CatLog.
Open a log.

Result: "main log" lines are shown instead of the actual file.

title: Add "Filter..." feature to the Record Log wizard
body: Users should be able to add filters for recording.

title: ICS compatibility
label: [Label(name="feature")]
body: Use Action Bar Sherlock for a real action bar that will work across Android versions.

title: OutOfMemoryError when opening extra large files
Investigate including ro.modversion in device information.
label: [Label(name="investigation")]
body: Seems to be available in the system/build.prop file.  May just be CyanogenMod-only.

title: Progress bar instead of indeterminate progress spinning animation
label: [Label(name="enhancement")]
body: Users love knowing how long a background task will take to complete.  There are lots of indeterminate progress dialogs that can be turned into analog progress bars that give a percentage display.

title: Don't force saving a log before sending as attachment.
body: Just save the damn log automatically.  Nobody wants to see an error message telling them what to do.

title: Send device information with logs.
body: Seems like a decent feature, when you're sending a log as an attachment.
